      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; analyst competency and simulation governance controls are addressed under SQA.",
      "rationale": "Formal use-error assessment is scoped out at MRL 2. Analyst qualification records and peer-review of simulation setup are maintained under the SQA framework, providing equivalent assurance at this risk level."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; model form uncertainty is bounded implicitly through validation output comparison.",
      "rationale": "Explicit model form uncertainty quantification (e.g., alternative turbulence model comparison) is not required at MRL 2. The output comparison factor provides indirect evidence that model form error is within acceptable bounds for the intended use."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; nominal input values with documented sources are sufficient.",
      "rationale": "Formal sensitivity analysis or uncertainty propagation on model inputs (viscosity, hematocrit, pump geometry tolerances) is not mandated at MRL 2. Nominal values are taken from published FDA benchmark specifications with traceable sources."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; sample characterization is addressed within the test conditions factor.",
      "rationale": "Detailed statistical characterization of experimental sample variability (e.g., inter-batch blood surrogate variation) is not required at MRL 2. Sample preparation protocols are documented in the FDA benchmark report and considered adequate."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; parameter equivalency between validation and COU scenarios is addressed qualitatively within the relevance of validation activities factor.",
      "rationale": "Formal equivalency mapping between validation input parameters and COU deployment parameters is not required at MRL 2. The relevance-of-validation-activities assessment confirms that the operating envelope, geometry, and fluid parameters are sufficiently equivalent for the intended credibility decision."
    }
  ],
